data.title: The Human Dutch
data.meta_description: In 1964, director Bert Haanstra set out to make a documentary about his native country of Holland. By focusing his camera on life's small moments -- a child going to school, a couple kissing in a park -- Haanstra reveals the deep emotional connections and community-minded manners that are singularly Dutch. He follows the quietly bustling lives of shopkeepers, housewives and everyday Dutch citizens to paint a portrait of a shy but very proud people.
